arXiv:2409.20381v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: This paper reports a search for a light CP-odd scalar resonance with a mass of 20 GeV to 90 GeV in 13 TeV proton-proton collision data with an integrated luminosity of 140 fb$^{-1}$ collected with the ATLAS detector at the Large Hadron Collider. The analysis assumes the resonance is produced via gluon-gluon fusion and decays exclusively into a $	au^{+}	au^{-}$ pair which decays into a fully leptonic $\mu^{+}
